intro: Lavoisiera quinquenervis, commonly known as the five-veined lavoisiera, is a species of flowering plant native to certain regions of Southeast Asia. It belongs to the family Araliaceae, which includes a variety of shrubs and trees. The plant is characterized by its compound leaves with five distinct veins, giving it its scientific name. It produces small, greenish-white flowers that are typically clustered in umbels. Lavoisiera quinquenervis is often found in moist, shaded environments such as forests and along stream banks.
